Event Listner
### Most seen are mouse event and keyboard event

takes 2 parameter Event and Function
		eg. button.addEventListener("click", function()
		{
			console.log("click!!!!!!")
		})
##for this we use 
 var button = document.getElementsByTagName("button")[0];
 not var button = document.getElementsByTagName("button")
  b/c it's an array

##To create a text -------->>> createTextNode
eg var li = document.createElement("li");
	li.appendChild(document.createTextNode("Testing"));
	ul.appendChild(li);
appendChild is for parent
main point from above is 
	createElement
	createTextNode
	appendChild to ul
example of take an input
	console.log(input.value)
	li.appendChild(document.createTextNode(input.value));


